===Etymology===
Believed to be a variation of {{m|en|Parthian shot}}, referring to a military maneuver in which [[Parthian]] troops retreating on horseback turned back to face the enemy and shot while retreating.<ref>{{R:Online Etymology Dictionary|Parthian}}</ref><ref>http://www.phrases.org.uk/bulletin_board/5/messages/1157.html</ref>

